Average weekly evictions since moratorium

ended, standardized by the population in poverty

Numbers represent the average weekly

eviction filings from Jan. 15, 2022 to

April 24, 2022 for each Manhattan

community district.

 

The median across the community

districts for average weekly evictions is

6, with a maximum of 16 (Community

District 12) and a minimum of 0

(Community District 5).

 

Community District 9 had,

on average,12 weekly eviction

filings.

Numbers represent the average

weekly eviction filings from Jan. 15, 2022

to April 24, 2022 for each Manhattan

community district, divided by the

population is living below the poverty

line and multiplied by 100,000.

 

(data collected from the New York City

Mayor’s office for economic opportunity)
